{"id":5125,"title":"Polytrauma in veterans: what does it mean for the medical-surgical nurse?","abstract":"Polytrauma in veterans has increased because improvements in medicine and technology have led to improved survival rates for individuals injured in armed conflicts. Medical-surgical nurses caring for today's veterans are faced with new patient needs. Rehabilitation using a multidimensional approach seems to be most effective in helping patients with polytrauma.","date":"2014-10-16","categories":"Wounds and Injuries","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25318333","annotations":[{"name":"Medicine","weight":0.701037,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Medicine"},{"name":"Physical medicine and rehabilitation","weight":0.264076,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Physical_medicine_and_rehabilitation"},{"name":"Technology","weight":0.107046,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Technology"},{"name":"Patient","weight":0.0561009,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patient"},{"name":"Nurse","weight":0.0494293,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nurse"},{"name":"War","weight":0.0370044,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War"},{"name":"Polytrauma","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Polytrauma"},{"name":"Veteran","weight":0.0185779,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Veteran"},{"name":"Dimension","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dimension"},{"name":"Mean","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mean"}]}
